summary:
My mission and core values are to advocate for social justice, dignity, multiculturality and togetherness. 

I'm committed to building communities in a spirit of solidarity and dialogue. I'm passionate about empowerment through connection and education,  supporting alternative narratives and making people´s stories heard and acknowledged. 

I am experienced in gender responsive training and analysis,  intercultural education, youth-led advocacy, project development and assessment, socio-psychological work with communities, qualitative and participatory-action research, sharing and building knowledge, designing learning strategies and theatre/drama facilitation. 

My work is guided by the Narrative Practices approach to counselling and community work.
I advocate for gender rights.
Physical theatre and body narratives are my heart.
